            <ab>To Salvius Timagenes, priest and archidikastes from Kronion � one of the inhabitants of the metropolis of the Arsinoite nome. I have lent to Herakleos and his brother � 600 silver drachmas, and when they had died before I received my loan back, the heirs Thenapunchis and Harmiusis ... (Here the papyrus breaks off.)</ab>
